[2] Ukraine
Date: 21 Dec 2011
Source: Med Novosti [In Russian, machine translation, edited]
http://medportal.ru/mednovosti/news/2011/12/21/measukr/

Measles outbreak in Ukraine
-----------------------
In Ukraine, a sharp increase in the incidence of measles has been
recorded. According to the State Sanitary and Epidemiological Service,
the largest number of cases had been observed in the Lviv region.
According to the agency on 20 Dec 2011 70 cases of infection were
registered in Ukrine. More than half the cases resided in the Lviv
region. In the Ivano-Frankivsk region 16 cases of measle were
recorded, 10 in the Volyn, 4 in in Rivne, and 2 in the Carpathian
region. Four suspected measles infection were recorded in Kiev.

During 2011 there have been 770 cases of measles in Ukraine. The
incidence of infection has risen sharply in some regions since early
December, acccordng to Interfax-Ukraine. In particular, in December
440 people wereinfected with measles in Lviv region, among them 178
children. Overall more than a hundred cases have been hospitalized. In
response, local authorities have restricted social gatherings and also
suspended classes at schools, where there hve been infections. In
addition, unvaccinated students have not been permitted to attend
classes.

In October 2011 the World Health Organization (WHO) reported an
epidemic of measles in the European region. According to WHO,
toutbreaks were reported in 40 out of 53 countries in the region.
Compared to the same period last year, the growth incidence rate was
276 percent.

