[3] Ukraine
Date: 21 Dec 2011
Source: Glared Stolitsa [In Russian, machine translation, edited]
http://stolitsa.glavred.info/archive/2011/12/21/161408-17.html

Measles epidemic reached Kiev
--------------------------
Four cases of suspected measles have been reorted in Kiev, according
to "Ukrainian News". The report stated that four members of an
organised tem were suspected cases of measles virus infectionon on 20
Dec 2011.

According to epidemiologists, 770 suspected cases of measles had be
recorded in Ukraine. In addition to Kiev, 503 cases recorded in the
Lviv region, 208 in Ivano-Frankivsk , 25 - in Volyn , 17 - in Rivne,
and 13 - in Transcarpathia. The Health authorities in western regions
have instituted a full range of control measures to prevent further
spread of the outbreak.

In particular, they have limited the holding of mass events, carried
outd medical examination of all contact persons who are not vaccinated
or do not have information on measles immunization status. Such
persons will be excluded from education, and classes at schools with
identified cases of measles,will be suspended.

On the recommendation of the Chief Medical Officer of the Lviv and
Ivano-Frankivsk regions immunoglobulin was purchased for the
emergency prevention of measles in persons in contact with measles .

The Glavred agency on 19 Dec 2011 were reported that there were 617
suspected cases of measles in the Lviv, Ivano-Frankivsk, Rivne, Volyn
and Transcarpathian regions. One person died from measles in the Lviv
region.

