[4] Philipinnes (Mindanao)
Dat: 21 Dec 2011
Source: Terra [In Spanish, machine translation, abridged & edited]
http://noticias.terra.com.ar/sociedad/autoridades-filipinas-advierten-sobre-brote-de-enfermedades,e25360c4c9e54310VgnVCM3000009af154d0RCRD.html

Disease outbreak warning
----------------------
The Philippine health authorities are warning about the risk of
outbreaks of disease in two cities in the south of the country
devastated by the recent floods, where the number of deaths has
already approaches 1000. The Department of Health said that it has
sent equipment to these places to combat respiratory other diseases
among displaced persons as a consequence of polluted water the the
insanitary conditions in the affectedcities -- the citie of Cagayan de
Oro and Iligan.

Health workers are vaccinating are vaccinating young persons against
measles, according to the Health Ministry.

At least 976 people died in the floods caused by tropical storm "
Washi" , and many persons are missing. More than 340 000 people have
been affected by the flooding. At least 44 000 of these victims are
housed in clearing centers with few comforts, while others encamp on
the streets.

